default3.
default20
default defaultCPL supports the introduction of biomass sustainability regulations but is concerned about confusion between the use of biomass to gdefaultenerate electricity, transport fuel and heat. defaultBiomass for heating and combined heat power is the most effective use of biomass
default. Generally speaking, using bioenergy for heat and power is more efficient in reducing GHG compared to using bioenergy for transpo
defaultrt fuel. Indeed, burning pure biomass to produce heat is 85% efficient; generating electricity by burning the same material is only approximately 30-35% efficient
